<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Wed 7 Mar 2007
From: Brent Barrett <salbrent@sbcglobal.net>
Source: Intervax News Agency, Russia & CIS [edited]
<http://www.interfax.com/3/248197/news.aspx>

Russia: Measles Outbreak Registered in Nizhny Novgorod
-----------------------------------------------
An outbreak of measles is taking place in Vyksa, located in Russia's
Nizhny Novgorod region. A total of 18 cases have been recorded in the
town since mid-February 2007, with 13 having been confirmed by
laboratory diagnosis. To stem the spread of the disease, over 5300
residents received measles vaccinations on 6 Mar 2007.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Information on the measles virus genotype present in the region
would be appreciated, if available, to relate this outbreak to recent
outbreaks elsewhere in Europe and beyond (see map on page 475 in the
WHO Weekly Epidemiological Record for 15 Dec 2006:
<http://www.who.int/wer/2006/wer815152/en/index.html>).
A map of Russia showing the city of Nizhny Novgorod to the northeast
of Moscow can be accessed at
<http://threesisters.gallery-forster.com/images/map_russia2.gif>. - Mod.CP]
